Specimen information

Clarity of UrineTranslucentUrine

Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy, though HbA1c is low. No evidence of urinary infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
